          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Peculiarities found by using different counting gases",
                " for Cf-252 spontaneuous fission."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "F.J.Hambsch",
                "J.Van Arle",
                "R.Vogt"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2ZZZGEL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "PHD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  A twin frisch gridded ionization chamber was",
                " used. The distance cathode - grid was 46 mm and the",
                " distance grid - anode was 12 mm. These dimensions were",
                " adapted in view of a working pressure of 0.6E+05 Pa.",
                " Both CH4 gas and a mixture of 90% argon and",
                " 10% CH4 were used as counter gases, with N55",
                " quality at pressures of 0.6E+05 Pa and 1.2E+05 Pa. At",
                " the lower pressure no absolute calibration using alpha",
                " particles from Cf-252 could be performed. The voltages",
                " applied to the chamber plates were -2.5 kV on the",
                " cathode and +2.1 kv on the anode for both counter",
                " gases at 0.6E+05 Pa. For the 1.2E+05 Pa pressure the",
                " voltages were -2.5 kV on the cathode and +2.1 kV on",
                " the anode for the gas mixture, and -2.5 kV on the",
                " cathode and +2.1 kV on the anode and -4.7 kV on the",
                " cathode and +4.0 kV on the anode for CH4."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The Cf-252 sample was mounted on a 0.12 mg/cm2 nickel",
                " backing in the center of the common cathode."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The data were corrected for electronic instabilities",
                " and different calibration factors between the four",
                " electronic chains. The frisch grid inefficiency was",
                " also taken into account. The angle-dependent energy",
                " loss in the sample and backing was experimentally",
                " determined and incorporated in the analysis. Mass",
                " dependent corrections for the pulse height defect,",
                " PHD, were applied."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  No comment"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".This is an investigation of how the determined",
                " quantities depend on the choice of counting gas. It",
                " was found that the mixture 90% argon and",
                " 10% CH4 gave the most reliable results."
              ]
            }
          ],
